{
  "stem": "9590.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And for almost a year and a half, he was presiding over the kolkhoz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "People came to ask him advice, and he gave them very practical answers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He was a person that felt for people, helped people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And they were-- the authorities and the people were very pleased with him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I was in school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "There weren't many changes, except that-- that the curriculum, everything was done in the Russian language.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "In a way, I was pleased to learn the Russian language because it is a beautiful language.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And when I was still in public school-- and I loved to read-- I read the Russian classics; Pushkin's, Dostoyevsky's, Tolstoy.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I read it in the Polish translation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And now that I acquired the knowledge of the Russian language, I read it in the original, and it was beautiful.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And this is how life was for us 'til June of 1941, when Hitler broke the pact with Russia, and he proceeds in the aggressive pact to go invade it again, Russia.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "By the way, my brother was home, and he was still much younger, so he went still to public school.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "They also learned everything in the Russian language.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And he also kept on with the Hebrew studies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I was the one that was out of town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] June 1941 is a date that is, in my memory, the turning point in my life.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Life changed from that day on to such an extent that nobody in their wildest dreams would be able even to-- to fantasize how life can change.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
